FBIS4-40748 "drsov118_b_94013" FBIS-SOV-94-118 Daily Report 17 Jun 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Plan To Merge Intelligence Agencies Rumored Plan To Merge Intelligence Agencies Rumored PM1706114194 Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA in Russian 17 Jun 94 p 1 PM1706114194 Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA Russian BFN [Untitled "Own Information" report] [Text] NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA has learned from unofficial sources that Federal Counterintelligence Service [FCS] chief S. Stepashin is aware of plans to merge the Main Protection Directorate, which is accountable to the president, and the FCS. But it is not yet known who will be the new department's chief -- Barsukov (Main Protection Directorate) or Stepashin himself. However, in his memoirs B. Yeltsin gave a high appraisal of the Kremlin commandant's flair and professionalism.
